[SN]TITLE[SN]
Owner fined for mouldy food at Porthmadog restaurant

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A restaurant owner has been fined for having a substantial amount of out-of-date mouldy food which was intended for sale, Gwynedd council said.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Harbour restaurant in Porthmadog was also found to have inadequate controls to prevent cross contamination and poor standards of cleanliness.
Restaurant owner David Paton pleaded guilty to seven food hygiene offences at Caernarfon Magistrates' Court.
He has to pay Â£5,000 plus nearly Â£1,300 in court costs.
The case was brought by the council's public protection service.
